text: Diana Ifeoma Ude (born 1986 in Enugu, Nigeria) is a Polish singer. She is the daughter of a Polish mother and a Nigerian father of the Ibo-people. She came to Poland at the age of three, where she lived with her maternal grandmother in Opole. She studied culture at Warsaw University. She was one of the ten participants in the Polish national final for the Eurovision Song Contest 2018, performing the song "Love is Stronger".
